  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: issues found and to be fixed for https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/1526\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n- [x]  CR code should not be scrollable and must be centered.\r\n- [x]  Wallet amount is not shown\r\n- [x]  Amount field doesn't highlight in focus\r\n- [x]  Contacts screen looks wrong on Android (2.1 can't be fixed because https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/7474)\r\n- [ ]  Amount rules (let's create separate issue for this because design is needed)\r\n\r\n## 1. iOS/Android:\r\n\r\nCurrently max length of the amount: 15 characters including separator (./,). This is different from the amount user can type for /send command in chat. It should be consistent in both places and seems like Wallet is a place to adjust:\r\n1.1 Expected: Amount before separator - seems like can be of any length or I can't find the limit\r\n1.2 Expected: Amount after separator - should be not more than 18 digits after comma (e.g 0.123456789012345678). Currently, it's possible to enter only 13 digits after comma (e.g. 0.1234567890123)\r\n1.3 \"0\" is now not allowed as a sum to send. In some cases, it's valid to send \"0\" (e.g https://contribute.status.im/sgt.html ), so it should be fine to request it too.\r\n\r\n## 2. Android\r\n2.1. Select contact screen, top part with phone icons (carrier, battery status, time) is on black background. Expected: white background, black text/icons\r\n2.2 There is some empty space between \"Contacts\" heading\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/30420588-b37e1832-9942-11e7-8f23-07e75916a712.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.10-98-g82f6a82b+\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
